1/4/01
  BUG: logical error found in procMaintainReq().  For large requested black 
       time, procMaintainReq() will always insert 15 pictures!
       Should only enough number of pictures to statmux!

  New procMaintainReq() algo:
      if (BG ready && request black completed)
          procEntryPoint()
      else {
          newFillTime = curTime + 0x6000;
          endBlackTime = channel stop time + reqBlackTime;
          if (request black not completed && endBlackTime<newFillTime)
              newFillTime = endBlackTime;
          fillChan(newFillTime);
      }

  It turns out that the new procMaintainReq() cause more severe audio lip sync
  problem.  The old one has about 50% chance of lip sync problem.  The new
  one almost always has it.

  Wayne mentioned that the audio code may fail if the gap is longer than 1 sec.
  Need new design to solve the problem.

  Jinbo wants DPI to return correct statistics to PPC.

