2/9/01

  More timing analysis:
    - MAX_BG_PIC_QUE_SIZE:
        - for net->ad, since ad should start at first frame, the value
          shouldn't matter
        - for ad->net, the value should cover the worst case GOP size,
          which should be 15 frames.

  A major problem is identified:
    Since we will store up to about 1/2 sec of BG material, the first entry
    point will mostly have a delay of up to 1/2 sec.o

    New scheme uses exactly the same algorithm, but much smaller parameters.
    MAX_TS_DELAY: assume one anchor unit is at most 3+2 fld time,
                  5/60 = 1/12 sec, allow same margin for the Ad's I frame
                  to be display ahead of the request splice time,
                  this gives 1/6 sec, or 5 frames. 

  The new parameters have a problem, for non-seamless splice,
  after channel maintain, BG never catch up with FG!

