2/14/00
  Emma's overnight test shows no reset, but lots of forced switches!
  Asked Matt to check in mux fix.

  3pm: compiled ver 1173.  Preview for next build.

  Did find that the forced switches are caused by the first pictures in ad
  being dropped.  To avoid this problem, new queue cleaning method is used
  for BG_READY mode:
      Instead of using picture in queue, use the estimated tsDelay time!
  Need to rework the Ready queue clean up mechanism:
  For FG, we actually don't need clean up as it will be done on demand,
    kind of like garbage collection.
  For BG, it is more important, since it will affect the tsDelay after the
    switch.  However, since there is no direct relationship between queue size
    and tsDelay, we should use the latter to determine when to flush the queue.

  For FG, spliceTime is initially set to the requested splice time
  in time mode.  Then it is adjusted to be the candidate exit time.

  => dpi1180.fls

  Noticed that the ad beginnig is dropped, not because of the queue flush
  code in procBgReady(), but in procBgSeek().  Since the MAX_TS_DELAY is now
  too narrow, with BG splice time set to FG splice time - MAX_TS_DELAY, there
  is still change for entry anchor's DET to be less than BG splice time.
  Seems we need to increase MAX_TS_DELAY.

  Note: Ver 1174 is compiled with view ytse-dpi.  Will check in changes
        if everything OK.


