3/1/01
  Noticed that Emma's station has forced switch every time on the ABC channel
  after running for a long time.
  Those forced switches are caused by dropping ad.
  The ABC channel has black pictures.

  Try to remove those forced switches by including EOS as a condition for
  exit candidate in picture based splice mode.  This was previously added
  just under the NCUBE flag.  The NCUBE flag has now been removed.

  The real reason for this continuous forced switch is that:
    After forced switch back to network, the network channel has 0 tsDelay.
    Lower delay means network channel will become ready later.
    The SeaChange Ad starts about 0.16 sec before the request splice time.
    Since MAX_TS_DELAY is 0.25 sec, this means any adjustment of splice time
    by more than 0.25 - 0.16 = 0.09 sec will cause dropping of ad frames!

    In normal case, the positive tsDelay in network channel is helping the
    channel to be ready earlier, 


