  The Cox's problem is because Jim did not update the environment file.
  It is using the 2.3.8DP environment file on 2.4.9DP.  Since flash partition
  has been changed, the code is not correctly loaded to the DSP.

  Learned how to use the bootp server to update code:
    Need to point the bootp server to the appropriate ini file.
    In the ini file, need to specify the release directory.
    Since TFTP server will be used for actual data transfer, and TFTP requires
    a root directory, both the bootp ini file and the release directory must
    be under the same TFTP root directory.

