12/11/01
  Studied Visual World's document
  Things to do to support:
    - need (higher speed) pass thru mode operation (no requant) through demux.
    - need to support multiple video streams per program
    - clean cut may be an issue (not necessary if input is already clean cut)
    - PMT to reflect worst case content

  It seems to me that if STB can handle time base change at splice point
  seamlessly, then we don't even need to restamp.  We can simply pass the
  whole SPTS thru demux with only send time adjustment.  Risk is high though.
  May need significant mux change, since the switch over point from normal
  operation to pass thru may not be aligned with scheduler.  Also mux must
  be able to handle DTS jump.

  Spot On seems to refer to TP level splicing!


12/12/01
  DPI conference:
    Spent most time on the discussion of ATSC DCC and its implication to
    DPI, and amount of involvement DPI group needs to be in it.

  Studied how memByteCopy() works.  It can handle the generic cases where
  the buffer start points may not be word aligned!
  Seems we can simplify it a great deal, if we assume all buffers start
  at word boundaries.
  Should try the assembly version memByteCpy() in kernal to see if it works!

  Also noticed that separateTp() may not work the way it should be.
  When it separates the TP, it move the PES header to the earlier TP,
  not the later.  This does not agree with MPEG spec!


12/13/01
  See whether the separateTp issue has anything to do with Digitran splice
  artifact, and the beating problem with DCT1000.

  Turn off audio PID, and use EOS for Digitran.

  Strange bug in upgrading RC:
    Found out that it is because in sending the NEW_STATQUE message to mux,
    the output task uses the sizeof(PicStat) for the message size.
    Since size of PicStat is very close to overflowing this field, increasing
    it will corrupt the message header.
    Solution is to use MSGSZ_PICSTAT_COMMON instead.

  Mux changes since DP3:
    11/01	CSCdv76717	Elementary buffer incompliance
    11/09	CSCdv83703	Improve max bit rate
    11/12	CSCdt85667	PCR jitter
    11/12	CSCdv86147	Digitran dropout


