12/18/01
  RC study:
    Noticed that I picture target miss has high correlation with window size,
    which is 1/128 of the picture size in bits.

    Try using a larger, fixed window size of 50000 bits:
      Seems for some scene blocking is gone, but in some scene blocking
      is still seen.

    Try suppressing QS code diff of +/- 1.  Result is worse.  Blurry picture,
      with bad blocks around edges sometimes.
    First result seems to have the mistake!

  Other idea for improving RC:
    - separate treatment of intra/inter macroblocks
    - skip MQUANT when MQUANT is reasonably high, and difference is small
    - different mapping from target ratio to new quant
